President Obama made calls to President Karzai, Dr. Abdullah, and Ambassador Eikenberry to discuss the recent developments related to the Afghan elections. He expressed his appreciation for President Karzai's decision to accept the certification of the election results and to agree to a second round of voting. President Obama emphasized that this decision was in the best interests of the Afghan people and reiterated the United States' commitment to an outcome that reflects the will of the Afghan people. He also thanked Dr. Abdullah for his constructive efforts. President Obama received an update from Ambassador Eikenberry and expressed his gratitude for their hard work. He also mentioned his appreciation for Senator John Kerry's collaboration with the Ambassador.